oai_dc:dc.dc:title: A Comparison of Pregnancy Detection by Palpation and a Blood Test in Dairy Cattle
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Breed, M. W.
Warnick, L. D.
Guard, C. L.
Smith, M. C.
White, M. E.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: bovine pregnancy
artificial insemination
rectal palpation
ELISA
enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay
pregnancy-specific protein B
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The purpose of this project was to compare the results of a blood test for bovine pregnancy with pregnancy detection by rectal palpation by veterinarians in dairy herds using artificial insemination. The blood test evaluated was a commercially-available enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay (ELISA) which tests for pregnancy-specific protein B.
